http://www.turkeydog.org/
There is one error that I know of in this article. While a number of State's departments of natural resources, fish &amp; game departments (or whatever the state calls their department), trapped and transplanted turkeys beginning in the 1950's, the National Wild Turkey Federation (NWTF) did not ever trap and transplant turkeys, since the only ones authorized to do that are the state game departments. The NWTF donated the cardboard boxes used to transport the birds as well as providing other assistance. And since the NWTF was not founded until 1973, their assistance came later. The restoration of the wild turkey was declared 'broadly successful' in 1966 by A.W. Schorger. By 1967, The Wildlife Society declared it 'spectacularly successful' nationwide. After that the majority of the wild turkeys growth was from natural breeding. Source: http://www.turkeydog.org/

